# Connection multiplexing only on macOS/Linux desktops. Two platforms opt out:
#   - Windows: OpenSSH has no Unix-socket ControlMaster support and dies with
#     "getsockname failed: Not a socket". `uname` is absent from the cmd.exe
#     PATH that runs Match exec, so exec fails and multiplexing stays off.
#   - Termux/Android: $HOME (/data/data/com.termux/files/home) is so long the
#     control-socket path overflows the ~108-char Unix-socket limit
#     ("unix_listener: path too long"). `uname -a` says "Android" there, so
#     `grep -qv Android` fails and multiplexing stays off.
Match originalhost macmini,macmini-tunnel,rog,rog-tunnel exec "uname -a | grep -qv Android"
  ControlMaster auto
  ControlPath ~/.ssh/control-%n-%C
  ControlPersist 8h
